snippet.textDisplay: First off with your hair you should either use mouse or hairspray. I prefer mouse extra gold even though I have curly hair because it helps my specific curls stay the way I prefer them. I would stick to super small curls because of your hair being so thick and long it will weigh the curl down which is part of the reason they fall out (I also have this very same issue). Once you curl the section, hold the curl in the curled position (do not let it fall), and then take a Bobby pin with each curl until you are completely done. Once they have set and you can spray them with hair spray and let them down. They should last a little longer. My hair is naturally ringlet curls and because my hair is so thick and long it weighs it down.
